                  <interp inst="t18200918-216-crimeloc1249" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-216-off1246 t18200918-216-crimeloc1249"></join>. On the 9th of August, I found the prisoner in custody with this floorcloth, which is mine,</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-216-person2116">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PEARSON
               <interp inst="t18200918-216-person2116" type="surname" value="PEARSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-216-person2116" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-216-person2116" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a broker, and live in Old-street. On the 8th of July, between ten and eleven o'clock, the prisoner brought this floorcloth for sale, and asked 6 s. for it-it is worth 21 s., which made me suspect him. I asked him where he got it? he said a man sent him to sell it; I told him to send the man. He left the shop, went a step or two up the road, and loitered about for ten minutes. I kept my eye upon him. He returned and said the man was not at home, and demanded the floorcloth, or if I would buy it, I should have it for 5 s. I detained him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
